cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with anomaly detection in traffic videos using machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the challenges faced in improving performance, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The use of machine learning algorithms for anomaly detection also suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also deals with video processing, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of anomaly detection, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category.
